Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.08,0:00:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Warm greetings to one and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.79,0:00:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The final session of our “Powerful by Faith!”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.79,0:00:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Regional Convention is about to begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.38,0:00:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,As you watch the music-video presentation,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.71,0:00:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,reflect on how strong faith
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.05,0:00:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,helps us triumph\Nwhen our integrity is tested.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.05,0:00:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Please enjoy the video.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.25,0:10:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We have now reached\Nthe final portion of this convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.13,0:10:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In this session,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.17,0:10:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll see how Bible prophecy\Nstrengthens our faith
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.93,0:11:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll take an exciting look ahead\Nat future events.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.06,0:11:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,First, let’s sing a song that expresses
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.23,0:11:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,our determination to exercise faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.39,0:11:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The song is number 126, entitled
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.52,0:11:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“Stay Awake, Stand Firm, Grow Mighty.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.57,0:11:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, that’s song number 126.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.24,0:13:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Earlier, we saw how Daniel the prophet
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.12,0:13:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,showed faith as a young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.58,0:13:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What further tests lie ahead,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.12,0:13:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and how did Jehovah strengthen him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.29,0:13:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We now invite you\Nto watch Part II of the drama 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.92,0:13:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{s18}{nSerif}Daniel: A Lifetime of Faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.62,0:14:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.49,0:14:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hail Nebo, Ishtar,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.04,0:14:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and Marduk—greatest god of all!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.67,0:14:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yah!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.07,0:16:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Call the wise men.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.53,0:16:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Call the wise men!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.04,0:16:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t know what that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.46,0:16:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn’t appear to be an omen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.50,0:16:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s nothing in the books, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.00,0:16:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Are these all the wise men?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.59,0:16:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The best in the kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.38,0:16:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, I need to speak to the king!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.01,0:16:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The queen mother, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.68,0:16:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,O king, may you live on forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.98,0:16:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s a man in your kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.98,0:16:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,who has the spirit of the holy gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.61,0:16:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He will tell you the interpretation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.49,0:16:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is this man?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.61,0:16:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.33,0:16:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.99,0:16:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Who’s Daniel?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.25,0:17:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you Daniel?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.92,0:17:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I am, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.55,0:17:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve heard concerning you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.59,0:17:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that you’re able to provide interpretations.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.72,0:17:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you are able to read the writing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.43,0:18:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and make its interpretation known to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.22,0:18:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you will be clothed with purple,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.81,0:18:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a gold necklace will be placed around your neck,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.40,0:18:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will rule as the third one in the kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.32,0:18:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You may keep your gifts.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.65,0:18:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Give your presents to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.45,0:18:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I will read the writing to the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.37,0:18:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The Most High God granted to Nebuchadnezzar
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.96,0:18:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the kingdom and greatness
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.46,0:18:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and honor and majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.04,0:18:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But when his heart became haughty,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.34,0:18:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,he was brought down from the throne of his kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.68,0:18:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and his dignity was taken away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.31,0:18:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But you, Belshazzar—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.48,0:18:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You have not humbled your heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.06,0:18:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,although you knew all of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.90,0:18:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.53,0:18:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you exalted yourself against the Lord of the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.86,0:18:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You had them bring you the vessels of His house.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.83,0:19:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you and your nobles,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.83,0:19:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,your concubines and secondary wives
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.17,0:19:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,drank wine from them
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.17,0:19:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and praised the gods of silver and gold
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.21,0:19:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,—gods who see nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.84,0:19:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and hear nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.30,0:19:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and know nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.56,0:19:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But you’ve not glorified the God
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.31,0:19:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in whose hand is your breath
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.02,0:19:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and all your ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.48,0:19:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So the hand was sent from Him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.28,0:19:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the interpretation of the words:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.75,0:19:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,MENE:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.08,0:19:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,God has numbered the days of your kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.29,0:19:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and brought it to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.56,0:20:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,TEKEL:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.02,0:20:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You have been weighed in the balances
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.02,0:20:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and found lacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.99,0:20:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,PERES:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.16,0:20:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Your kingdom has been divided
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.33,0:20:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and given to the Medes
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.41,0:20:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Persians.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.08,0:21:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,King Darius, this is Daniel
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.38,0:21:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,—a Jew taken captive by the Babylonians.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.55,0:21:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you interpret the handwriting from the gods?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.34,0:21:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.93,0:21:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Not me, O king
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.43,0:21:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,—my God—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.64,0:21:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the God of Israel.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.02,0:21:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We could use a satrap
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.23,0:21:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,who understands the captives.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.61,0:21:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I confess, a satrap
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.61,0:21:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is not as prominent a position
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.32,0:21:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,as Belshazzar granted you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.03,0:21:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, Daniel refused
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.58,0:21:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,every gift and honor Belshazzar offered him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.71,0:21:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A man without a price.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.46,0:21:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t need you as a satrap
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.88,0:21:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,—we need you over them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.47,0:22:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Tura,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.01,0:22:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,pronounce Daniel’s appointment
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.01,0:22:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.89,0:22:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I want those stealing from the treasury to know
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.77,0:22:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that they will now be held accountable.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.05,0:22:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.38,0:22:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll make a fine high official.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.89,0:22:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Only with Jehovah’s help.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.41,0:23:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is the land tax so high?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.84,0:23:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Another revolt?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.26,0:23:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This is far more troubling.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.51,0:23:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I just collected the land tax from an administrator.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.01,0:23:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he pay?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.85,0:23:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but he refuses to give us “our fees.”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.64,0:23:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve had the same problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.06,0:23:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re calling anything more than the tax extortion.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.02,0:23:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s changed?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.69,0:23:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.03,0:23:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you offered him anything
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.86,0:23:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to make him more reasonable?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.57,0:23:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He won’t take a shekel of silver.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.33,0:23:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel claims that what he receives
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.04,0:23:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is more than enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.25,0:23:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t be so naive!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.25,0:24:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s putting on a show of integrity for the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.38,0:24:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It won’t last.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.96,0:24:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Darius will tire of him soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.22,0:24:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There seems to be a discrepancy in the taxes
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.23,0:24:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,due the treasury, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.40,0:24:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re brave to say that here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.44,0:24:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it’s hard to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.44,0:24:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We will review the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.82,0:24:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel, your time here has given you much wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.53,0:24:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,How long have you been here?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.95,0:24:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 70 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.20,0:24:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Share more with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.79,0:24:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me about the dreams
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.29,0:24:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,you interpreted for Nebuchadnezzar.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.29,0:24:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Interpretations belong to my God,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.96,0:24:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.46,0:24:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He revealed the dreams to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.85,0:25:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Have I really been in Babylon over 70 years?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.78,0:25:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremiah’s prophecy!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.63,0:25:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“When 70 years have been fulfilled,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.64,0:25:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will call to account the king of Babylon
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.22,0:25:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and that nation for their error.”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.35,0:25:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Belshazzar’s death
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.02,0:25:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,—it’s been fulfilled!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.62,0:26:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What does this mean for God’s people?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.94,0:26:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“When 70 years at Babylon are fulfilled,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.77,0:26:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will turn my attention to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.61,0:26:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“and I will make good my promise
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.16,0:26:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,by bringing you back to this place.”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.87,0:26:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Judah!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.01,0:26:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I must approach Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.01,0:26:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to confess the sin of my people.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.18,0:27:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,O Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.73,0:27:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,do hear,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.36,0:27:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,do forgive.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.36,0:27:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,O Jehovah, do pay attention and act.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.24,0:27:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not delay, for your own sake,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.12,0:27:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,O my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.33,0:27:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,O Daniel,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.84,0:27:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,now I have come to give you insight
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.21,0:27:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.63,0:27:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,When you began your entreaty,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.80,0:27:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the word went out,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.43,0:27:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and I have come to report it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.26,0:27:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,There are 70 weeks that have been determined
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.98,0:27:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,for your people and your holy city
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.02,0:27:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to terminate the transgression,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.02,0:27:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to finish off sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.28,0:28:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel, Azarel and Hannah are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.08,0:28:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.87,0:28:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s so good to see you!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.41,0:28:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Epher, come sit with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.25,0:28:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I have good news!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.17,0:28:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the good news?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.76,0:28:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has long told us
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.43,0:28:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that we will return to Judah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.76,0:28:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked again at Jeremiah’s prophecy:
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.10,0:28:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“This is what Jehovah says,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.65,0:28:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘When 70 years at Babylon are fulfilled, . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.86,0:28:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘I will make good my promise
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.49,0:28:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,by bringing you back to this place.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.03,0:28:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“Seventy years.”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.08,0:28:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That means God’s people will return soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.71,0:28:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you be sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.55,0:28:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah sent an angel to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.80,0:28:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,An angel?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.43,0:29:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that the city
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.80,0:29:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and its temple will be rebuilt,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.35,0:29:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Messiah will finally come!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.52,0:29:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You will get to see the temple rebuilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.06,0:29:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But won’t it be dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.98,0:29:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is eager
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.49,0:29:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to fulfill the needs of his people.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.95,0:29:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He told Isaiah
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.45,0:29:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that we ‘won’t bear children for distress,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.54,0:29:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,‘for they’re the offspring
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.83,0:29:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,made up of those blessed by Jehovah.’
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.38,0:29:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And if Jehovah says it,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.88,0:29:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s as good as done!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.17,0:29:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But isn’t the land desolate?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.09,0:29:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why we’ll need skilled builders
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.55,0:29:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,for the restoration work.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.51,0:29:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this mean you’ll return to Judah?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.15,0:29:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I sure hope so.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.78,0:30:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a team of workers maintain the roads.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.24,0:30:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, conditions will only worsen
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.29,0:30:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,during the rainy season.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.25,0:30:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Tura, see that it’s done.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.54,0:30:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it that you know so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.75,0:30:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t take credit, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.67,0:30:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I just . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.67,0:30:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We have many great men
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.67,0:30:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,who provide the information we need, O king.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.89,0:30:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.64,0:30:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,about that satrap in Susa.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.93,0:30:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Should he be replaced?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.73,0:30:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,My men have thoroughly investigated,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.61,0:30:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and the satrap has been diverting palace money
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.82,0:30:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to his own pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.90,0:30:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s—that’s impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.57,0:30:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t he your nephew, Otanes?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.82,0:30:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, and I can vouch for his integrity!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.04,0:30:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There must be some mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.29,0:30:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,How can Daniel know his character as I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.46,0:31:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I will speak with him and resolve the matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.51,0:31:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We Medes and Persians
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.09,0:31:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,are not as intolerant as these Jews.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.72,0:31:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure we can fix this.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.56,0:31:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. Settle it quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.43,0:31:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That will be all.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.89,0:31:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, I’m so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.81,0:31:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You have guests.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.11,0:32:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,All you Jews do is pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.29,0:32:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I could not serve the king
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.29,0:32:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the way I do without God’s help.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.33,0:32:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Serve the king
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.33,0:32:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,by intimidating satraps?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.42,0:32:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve only done what I should.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.42,0:32:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,An outsider has no place telling us
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.63,0:32:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,how to conduct business.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.14,0:32:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I act in the king’s interests.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.68,0:32:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve heard how you acted
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.06,0:32:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,in Nebuchadnezzar’s interests.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.81,0:32:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You made him go insane.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.60,0:32:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a message from Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.65,0:32:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Call it what you will,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.73,0:32:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,but do not interfere with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.28,0:32:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If it seemed easy
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.16,0:32:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to remove a satrap,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.91,0:32:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,think of how much easier it will be
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.20,0:32:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to get rid of an old Jew.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.90,0:33:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s an honor to be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.65,0:33:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know why I summoned you?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.11,0:33:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.40,0:33:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That satrap whose dismissal Daniel recommended
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.37,0:33:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,—what’s become of him?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.70,0:33:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we thoroughly investigated the matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.29,0:33:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Was there negligence?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.58,0:33:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,None.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.75,0:33:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Any omission of duty?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.13,0:33:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.46,0:33:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All taxes due the treasury have come to the treasury?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.76,0:33:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Every shekel of gold and quart (1.08 L) of beer
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.63,0:33:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,are accounted for.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.34,0:33:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel reached a different conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.10,0:34:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Daniel—
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.14,0:34:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He served the Babylonian kings well, but . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.06,0:34:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,he’s so old!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.19,0:34:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What Otanes means is,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.69,0:34:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,at Daniel’s age, how reliable is his judgment?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.28,0:34:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,His ideas are outdated.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.24,0:34:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, he is a Jew.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.03,0:34:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Katu, we are tolerant of all peoples.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.03,0:34:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, of course. That’s my point.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.37,0:34:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel, we were just talking about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.58,0:34:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You were right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.83,0:34:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s been a revolt in Susa.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.21,0:34:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They demand a new satrap
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.76,0:34:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,—one who doesn’t steal from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.67,0:34:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But my lord, surely . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.26,0:34:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.68,0:34:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I sent my own inspectors—men I trust!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.93,0:34:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel, you’ve distinguished yourself over these men.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.57,0:34:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine what I could do if you were my prime minister.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.41,0:34:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps we could approach the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.74,0:35:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s no use.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.37,0:35:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel’s manipulating him.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.37,0:35:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We need an accusation against Daniel
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.42,0:35:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,—something that Darius can’t ignore.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.42,0:35:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But no one has accused him of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.13,0:35:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.17,0:35:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Assemble a team to comb through our laws.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.51,0:35:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely he’s violated something.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.76,0:35:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.39,0:35:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Interview merchants, inspectors, officials
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.60,0:35:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,—whoever will make an accusation against him.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.77,0:35:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Assure the accuser
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.18,0:35:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,he will be generously rewarded.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.10,0:35:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We have the Babylonian records.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.27,0:35:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Search for any scandal that might implicate him.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.05,0:35:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing in the records.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.60,0:36:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.02,0:36:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a shekel of silver is missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.85,0:36:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, when Daniel gets involved,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.19,0:36:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,corruption and loss go down.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.03,0:36:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep searching.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.53,0:36:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No one will speak against him.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.87,0:36:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They all love him,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.04,0:36:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and he has the king’s trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.05,0:36:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually, the foreign merchants are ignored
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.72,0:36:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,when they experience theft.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.97,0:36:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Daniel stands up for them
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.31,0:36:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and investigates.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.14,0:36:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He has thieves return whatever was stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.48,0:36:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Even his friends are spotless.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.69,0:36:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Nebuchadnezzar once forbade anyone
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.69,0:36:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to speak against their God.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.70,0:37:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Supposedly,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.74,0:37:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,this “Jehovah” saved them from the furnace
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.45,0:37:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,when they refused to worship a Babylonian god.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.12,0:37:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Jews won’t worship other gods?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.96,0:37:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So it would seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.09,0:37:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you’ve solved our problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.22,0:37:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Katu, Otanes, what favor do you seek?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.30,0:37:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,O King Darius, may you live on forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.14,0:37:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This Babylon of which you are king
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.43,0:37:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is mighty but diverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.43,0:37:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There are Babylonians, Egyptians, Greeks, and others.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.90,0:37:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Otanes, I know these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.86,0:37:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the rightful king
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.86,0:37:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but also a foreigner and a newcomer.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.20,0:37:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The people must adapt,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.16,0:37:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,or the kingdom could become unstable.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.45,0:37:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you suggest?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.95,0:37:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,All royal officials,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.96,0:37:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,prefects, satraps,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.71,0:37:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,high royal officers, and governors
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.17,0:37:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,have consulted together to establish a royal decree
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.38,0:38:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and to enforce a ban
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.80,0:38:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that for 30 days, whoever makes a petition
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.72,0:38:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to any god or man
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.60,0:38:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,except to you, O king,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.68,0:38:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,should be thrown into the lions’ pit.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.64,0:38:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The people are not above rebellion.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.48,0:38:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Look what happened in Susa.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.65,0:38:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, O king,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.32,0:38:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,may you establish the decree and sign it
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.37,0:38:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,so that it cannot be changed,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.41,0:38:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,according to the law of the Medes and the Persians,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.04,0:38:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,which cannot be annulled.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.97,0:38:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,At this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.47,0:38:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,our empire experiences peace and prosperity
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.18,0:38:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,unlike ever seen before.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.27,0:38:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The recent acts of defiance in Susa,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.36,0:39:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,along with similar acts by small groups of radicals,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.69,0:39:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,seek to undermine
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.99,0:39:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,our way of life
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.99,0:39:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,—a way of life we will sacrifice for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.91,0:39:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In honor of the glorious freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.04,0:39:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,so kindly granted by the empire
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.75,0:39:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and as a reminder of its sovereignty,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.92,0:39:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I, Darius the Mede,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.05,0:39:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,make this decree:
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.09,0:39:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,For 30 days, anyone
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.67,0:39:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,who makes a petition to any god or man,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.39,0:39:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,except to the king,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.89,0:39:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,should be thrown into the lions’ pit.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.54,0:40:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re not going home to pray, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.88,0:40:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Azarel,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.09,0:40:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you know me,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.64,0:40:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and so do my enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.26,0:40:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I pray at my window three times a day,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.10,0:40:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.90,0:40:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If I even appear to compromise,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.36,0:40:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,what would they think?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.07,0:40:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That you stopped praying altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.87,0:40:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Or even worse,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.16,0:40:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that I’d trade my worship for my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.71,0:40:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I know Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.83,0:40:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I trust him,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.80,0:40:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,he’ll reward me.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.01,0:40:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t know how,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.01,0:40:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but he will.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.10,0:40:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray that I keep my faith
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.06,0:41:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,—that we all keep our faith—
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.90,0:41:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter how this ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.50,0:41:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I have something for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.56,0:41:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Dinner’s ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.86,0:41:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah is my light
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.95,0:41:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“and my salvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.95,0:41:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Whom should I fear?”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.17,0:42:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“Hear me, O Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.10,0:42:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“when I cry out.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.72,0:42:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“Show me favor
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.69,0:42:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“and answer me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.82,0:42:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“Your face, O Jehovah, I will seek to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.78,0:42:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“[For] you are my helper;
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.08,0:42:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“do not forsake me 
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.29,0:42:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“or leave me,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.38,0:42:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,my God of salvation.”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.20,0:44:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,O king, may you live on forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.25,0:44:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you not sign a ban
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.88,0:44:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,stating that for 30 days any man
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.25,0:44:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,who makes a petition to any god or man
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.84,0:44:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,—except to you, O king—
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.05,0:44:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,should be thrown into the lions’ pit?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.05,0:44:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the matter is well-established
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.05,0:44:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,according to the law of the Medes and the Persians.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.10,0:44:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s your business?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.14,0:44:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel, who is of the exiles of Judah,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.48,0:44:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,has paid no regard to you, O king,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.48,0:44:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,nor to the ban that you signed.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.36,0:44:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But three times a day,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.57,0:44:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,he is praying.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.04,0:44:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.55,0:45:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It can’t be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.01,0:45:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.68,0:45:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn’t even try to deny it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.48,0:45:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Were there witnesses?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.60,0:45:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All five of us, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.19,0:45:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We can attest to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.02,0:45:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But he is old.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.98,0:45:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Does he know what he’s doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.99,0:45:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,As a high official,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.99,0:45:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,surely he understands what it means
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.20,0:45:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to obey the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.04,0:45:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me be.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.04,0:45:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we arrest Daniel?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.62,0:45:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave the matter to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.97,0:46:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel should indeed be made an example of.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.60,0:46:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll remove him from his post
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.65,0:46:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and expel him from the city tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.98,0:46:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord . . . 
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.02,0:46:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All will learn that our laws must be obeyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.11,0:46:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But the law actually states that the accused
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.90,0:46:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,would be “thrown into the lions’ pit,” my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.24,0:46:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I see what you’re doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.45,0:46:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you no shame?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.45,0:46:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The law of the Medes and the Persians
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.21,0:46:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is that any ban or decree that the king establishes
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.04,0:46:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot be changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.09,0:47:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We only wish the king to receive the honor
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.47,0:47:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,he deserves.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.02,0:47:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Take him to the pit.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.01,0:49:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Your God, whom you are continually serving,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.80,0:49:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,will rescue you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.28,0:50:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Remove the stone!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.62,0:50:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.25,0:50:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.67,0:50:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,O king, may you live on forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.22,0:50:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.31,0:50:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring him up!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.10,0:50:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,My God sent his angel
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.60,0:50:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and shut the mouths of the lions,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.15,0:50:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and they have not harmed me,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.61,0:50:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,for I was found innocent before him;
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.45,0:51:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,nor have I done any wrong to you, O king.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.00,0:51:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Armenia is mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.09,0:51:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel let them off too easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.72,0:51:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We need their exceptional horses for our cavalry
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.80,0:51:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and a few for myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.56,0:51:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, you take Armenia.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.69,0:51:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I have my eye on Bactria and its precious stones.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.27,0:51:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Must you divide up Daniel’s kingdom now?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.53,0:51:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Check the back room!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.91,0:51:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.83,0:51:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You are being arrested
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.29,0:51:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,for crimes against Darius the king!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.12,0:51:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The king ordered Daniel’s arrest, not ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.96,0:51:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel was arrested
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.42,0:51:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and lifted from the pit this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.51,0:51:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,—unharmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.64,0:51:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It can’t be!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.18,0:52:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The lions must have already been fed.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.60,0:52:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps they were ill.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.81,0:52:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The lions were ill?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.31,0:52:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Not hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.28,0:52:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Throw them and their families into the pit,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.28,0:52:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,where they can test their theories.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.16,0:52:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Darius!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.25,0:52:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t do this! I served you!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.29,0:52:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Don’t do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.75,0:52:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I served you!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.38,0:52:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.84,0:52:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.72,0:52:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I am issuing an order
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.51,0:52:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that in every domain of my kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.72,0:52:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,people are to tremble in fear
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.85,0:52:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,before the God of Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.52,0:52:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,For he is the living God, and he endures forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.44,0:52:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,His kingdom will never be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.44,0:52:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“He rescues,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.69,0:52:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“saves, and performs signs and wonders
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.40,0:52:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“in the heavens and on the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.95,0:53:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,for he rescued Daniel from the paw of the lions.”
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.74,0:53:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Darius wrote that?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.37,0:53:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s sending it to all of his subjects.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.54,0:53:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We were so worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.83,0:53:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you scared?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.96,0:53:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I was very scared,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.96,0:53:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehovah helps us when we’re scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.76,0:53:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re scared of going to Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.68,0:53:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Epher!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.85,0:53:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re still thinking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.56,0:53:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How about you? Are you going back?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.98,0:53:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The king says we’re all allowed to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.07,0:53:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d love to go home,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.29,0:53:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.63,0:54:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it’s too late for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.23,0:54:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I don’t want to go either.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.27,0:54:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.32,0:54:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.99,0:54:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If you go,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.03,0:54:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll see a better city than the one I left.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.83,0:54:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll see prophecies fulfilled,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.54,0:54:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a city full of people worshipping Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.63,0:54:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and a new temple
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.80,0:54:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,—the most beautiful building on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.45,0:55:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see our old neighbor at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.37,0:55:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I didn’t him at all today.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.71,0:55:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw our neighbor Eli the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.17,0:55:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay close to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.17,0:56:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be blessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.18,0:56:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“One thing
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.18,0:56:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“I have asked from Jehovah . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.61,0:56:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“that I might dwell
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.41,0:56:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“in the house of Jehovah all the days of my life,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.71,0:56:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“to gaze
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.76,0:56:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“upon the pleasantness of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.35,0:57:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“and to look
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.77,0:57:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“with appreciation
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.61,0:57:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,on his temple.”
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.59,0:58:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel, you need to rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.98,0:59:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,O Daniel, you very precious man.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.53,0:59:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I have been sent to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.65,0:59:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not be afraid, Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.03,0:59:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Your words have been heard from the first day
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.62,0:59:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you gave your heart to understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.70,0:59:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and humbling yourself before your God.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.25,0:59:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I have come to make you understand
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.25,0:59:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,what will befall your people
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.25,0:59:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,in the final part of the days.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.25,0:59:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.96,0:59:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no breath left in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.09,0:59:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not be afraid, O very precious man.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.51,0:59:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,May you have peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.05,0:59:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Be strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.39,0:59:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Be strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.53,0:59:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Let my lord speak,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.91,0:59:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,for you have strengthened me.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.24,1:00:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I will tell you the things recorded
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.45,1:00:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in the writings of truth:
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.45,1:00:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“Look!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.66,1:00:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“Three more kings will stand up for Persia,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.37,1:00:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the fourth one will amass greater riches
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.96,1:00:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,than all others.”
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.40,1:00:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,O my lord,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.23,1:00:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,what will be the outcome of these things?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.36,1:00:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Happy is the one who keeps in expectation.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.99,1:00:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on to the end.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.78,1:00:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You will rest,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.49,1:00:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,but you will stand up for your lot
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.50,1:00:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,at the end of the days.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.60,1:01:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If we eat those foods, we’ll disobey our God.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.94,1:01:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You fear your God?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.94,1:01:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.15,1:01:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Interpretations belong to my God, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.82,1:01:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that he will reveal it to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.99,1:01:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.66,1:01:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is eager to fulfill the needs of his people.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.80,1:01:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I know Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.47,1:01:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I trust him,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.94,1:01:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,he’ll reward me.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.78,1:02:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t know how,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.00,1:02:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but he will.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.89,1:02:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What an inspiring account!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.93,1:02:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Daniel,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.98,1:02:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we look to Jehovah\Nfor strength and protection.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.31,1:02:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Our next song expresses\Nour confidence in him.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.07,1:02:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The song is entitled\N“Seek God for Your Deliverance.”
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.49,1:02:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s sing together song number 150.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.20,1:02:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, that’s song number 150.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.91,0:00:17.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんを歓迎いたします
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.12,0:00:23.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,「信仰によって強くなる」地区大会の\N最後の部が始まります
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.04,0:00:26.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,次のミュージックビデオを見ながら
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.80,0:00:32.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,忠誠が試みられる時に\N信仰がどう役立つか考えましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.26,0:00:34.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,ビデオをお楽しみください
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.29,0:10:50.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,今年の地区大会も\N残りわずかとなりました
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.75,0:10:56.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,この部では 聖書の預言が\Nどのように信仰を強めるかを考え
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.38,0:11:00.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,将来起こる素晴らしい事柄\Nについて取り上げます
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.56,0:11:06.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず 信仰を持ち続けるという\N決意を表す歌を歌いましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.52,0:11:08.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,126番の歌で
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.56,0:11:14.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,題は「目を覚ましていて\Nしっかり立ち 強い人になる」です
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.11,0:11:17.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,126番の歌を歌いましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.49,0:13:29.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,ドラマの第1部で 若い時の\Nダニエルの信仰を見ました
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.87,0:13:35.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後どんなことがあり エホバは\Nどのようにダニエルを助けたでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.79,0:13:42.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,「ダニエル 信仰を貫いた人」という\Nドラマの第2部をご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.39,0:14:50.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,あったぞ！
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.06,0:14:54.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネボ イシュタル マルドゥク！
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.06,0:14:56.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,偉大な神々に乾杯！
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.56,0:14:58.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,乾杯！
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.05,0:16:09.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,賢人たちを呼べ
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.47,0:16:13.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,賢人たちを呼ぶんだ！
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.81,0:16:20.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,何だこれは？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.48,0:16:21.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,お告げでもなさそうだ・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.94,0:16:23.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,こんなものは見たことがない
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.40,0:16:25.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかに賢人はいないのか！
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.44,0:16:27.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,これで全員です
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.74,0:16:31.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,王に会わせてください
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.45,0:16:37.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,母上さまがいらっしゃいました
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.00,0:16:41.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,王がいつまでも生き続けますように
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.25,0:16:46.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,この王国には 聖なる神々の\N力を持つ人がいます
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.67,0:16:49.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼なら解き明かせるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.89,0:16:51.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰ですか
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.64,0:16:53.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルです
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.43,0:16:57.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル？知らない
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.56,0:17:44.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルか？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.98,0:17:47.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうです
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.40,0:17:50.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,聞くところによると
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.45,0:17:53.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは解き明かしができるそうだな
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.78,0:17:59.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,もし この文字を読んで\N意味を解き明かせるなら
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.79,0:18:03.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたに紫の衣を着せ
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.59,0:18:06.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,金の首飾りを掛け
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.30,0:18:09.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,この王国の第3の地位を与えよう
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.51,0:18:11.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,贈り物は必要ありません
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.01,0:18:14.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,褒美はほかの人にお与えください
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.01,0:18:19.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですが 私はこの文字を\N王にお読みします
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.60,0:18:22.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,至高の神はネブカドネザルに
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.31,0:18:27.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,王国と偉大な力と\N栄誉と威光を与えました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.11,0:18:30.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 心が傲慢になった時
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.90,0:18:33.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,王座から降ろされ
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.66,0:18:37.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,尊厳を奪われました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.67,0:18:46.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,ところが あなたベルシャザルは
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.00,0:18:51.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,この全てを知りながら\N謙遜になっていません
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.55,0:18:55.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,かえって 天の主に対して高ぶり
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.35,0:18:59.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,その神の家の器を持ってこさせました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.85,0:19:03.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして あなたと貴族たち
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.85,0:19:08.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,また側室やそばめたちは\Nそれを使ってぶどう酒を飲み
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.44,0:19:12.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,銀や金でできた神々を賛美しました
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.15,0:19:17.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,その神々は見ることも\N聞くこともできません
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.04,0:19:22.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん何も知りません
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.71,0:19:26.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,それなのにあなたは
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.29,0:19:30.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの命を支えている\N神をたたえてはいません
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.67,0:19:33.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのため 手が
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.89,0:19:37.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,神から送られたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.18,0:19:42.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,意味を解き明かしましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.98,0:19:46.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,メネ
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.31,0:19:50.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,神はあなたの王国の
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.11,0:19:53.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,日数を数えて終わらせた
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.54,0:20:04.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,テケル
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.17,0:20:09.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたはてんびんで量られて
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.09,0:20:12.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,不足があった
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.22,0:20:19.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,ペレス
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.43,0:20:23.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,王国は分けられて
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.56,0:20:26.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,メディア人と
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.27,0:20:29.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,ペルシャ人に与えられた
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.90,0:21:12.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダリウス王 ダニエルです
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.23,0:21:15.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,バビロンに連れてこられたユダヤ人です
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.62,0:21:22.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたが文字を あの文字を\N解き明かしたのか？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.54,0:21:24.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいえ
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.79,0:21:27.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,私ではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.50,0:21:32.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の神 イスラエルの神です
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.13,0:21:37.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,別の民族のことが分かっている\N知事がいると助かる
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.30,0:21:44.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,いや待てよ 知事だとベルシャザルの\N申し出た立場よりも格が低い
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.39,0:21:50.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルはベルシャザルが\N申し出た褒美を断っています
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.61,0:21:55.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,こんな人物がいたのか
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.78,0:21:58.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,知事ではもったいない
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.41,0:22:02.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたには知事たちを監督してもらおう
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.46,0:22:10.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,トゥラ このことを帝国中に\N知らせなさい
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.29,0:22:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,公費を横領している者たちを\N取り締まってもらおう
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.08,0:22:46.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル あなたが高官だと安心です
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.41,0:22:49.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに頼るしかありません
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.36,0:23:19.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,この土地の税金は高過ぎる
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.95,0:23:27.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,また払わないやつがいるのか？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.29,0:23:29.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,面倒なことになってます
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.33,0:23:31.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,役人が集めた土地の税金なんですけど
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.83,0:23:33.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちゃんと持ってきたのか？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.25,0:23:34.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,はい
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.38,0:23:36.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも“手数料”は入ってませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.55,0:23:38.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,うちもそうだ
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.34,0:23:41.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,決められた額以上は\N収めないと言うんです
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.43,0:23:43.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうしてだ？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.64,0:23:46.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルのせいだな！
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.14,0:23:48.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルには たんまり\N持たせてるんだろう？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.94,0:23:51.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,何も受け取ろうとしません
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.27,0:23:55.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,全く欲がないみたいです
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.23,0:23:57.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,そんな訳ないだろう！
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.28,0:24:00.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,今は王の前で格好付けてるだけだ
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.41,0:24:02.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,気にするな
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.78,0:24:05.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのうちぼろが出る
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.42,0:24:18.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,国の税の扱いに不備があるようです
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.09,0:24:21.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうか よく言ってくれた
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.97,0:24:24.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,残念な話ですが
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.39,0:24:26.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,この件は調査させよう
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.81,0:24:30.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル あなたはかなり\N経験を積んでいるようだが
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.35,0:24:32.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここに来て長いのか？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.02,0:24:35.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,かれこれ70年です
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.86,0:24:37.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,教えてくれないか
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.86,0:24:41.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたがネブカドネザルに\N解き明かした夢のことを
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.36,0:24:44.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,解き明かすのは私の神エホバです
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.78,0:24:48.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが明らかにしてくださったのです
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.38,0:25:03.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,バビロンに来て70年か
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.22,0:25:10.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうだ エレミヤの預言だ
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.58,0:25:32.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,「70年が満了した時
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.17,0:25:38.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は 過ちを犯したバビロンの\N王と国民に責任を問う」
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.50,0:25:42.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベルシャザルが殺されたことだ
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.05,0:25:45.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,預言通りだ！
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.74,0:26:04.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の民はどうなるんだろう？
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.68,0:26:27.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,「バビロンで70年が満了したら
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.76,0:26:31.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,私はあなたたちに注意を向ける
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.18,0:26:35.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の約束を果たし
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.52,0:26:40.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたたちをこの場所に連れ戻す」
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.07,0:26:45.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダの地だ！
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.33,0:26:53.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに祈り
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.71,0:26:57.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,イスラエルの罪を告白しなくては
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.42,0:27:04.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバ
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.76,0:27:07.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,聞いてください
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.64,0:27:10.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,お許しください
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.26,0:27:13.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちに注意を向けて
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.14,0:27:15.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,救ってください！
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.81,0:27:18.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたご自身のために
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.69,0:27:22.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,行動を遅らせないでください
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.36,0:27:28.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.78,0:27:34.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,私はあなたに洞察と理解を\N与えるために来ました
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.21,0:27:38.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたが懇願し始めた時に
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.29,0:27:41.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,神が述べられた言葉を伝えに来ました
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.13,0:27:46.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの民と聖なる都市のために\N70週が定められました
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.84,0:27:51.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは 違反を終わらせ\N罪をなくし⋯⋯
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.06,0:28:02.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル アザルエルと\Nハンナが来ましたよ
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.19,0:28:04.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,こんにちは
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.11,0:28:06.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,よく来たね！
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.32,0:28:08.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,エフェル こっちへおいで
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.03,0:28:11.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいことがあったんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.12,0:28:16.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,何があったんですか？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.46,0:28:23.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは昔 私たちがユダに\N戻れるとおっしゃった
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.59,0:28:27.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,エレミヤの預言をもう一度確かめたんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.26,0:28:32.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバはこう言う
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.85,0:28:36.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,『バビロンで70年が満了したら
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.14,0:28:39.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は⋯⋯約束を果たし
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.19,0:28:43.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたたちをこの場所に連れ戻す』」
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.57,0:28:45.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,「70年」とあるから
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.86,0:28:48.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,もうすぐ帰れるということだ
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.49,0:28:51.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうして分かったんですか？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.29,0:28:56.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,天使が来て教えてくれたんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.79,0:28:59.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,天使が来たの？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.13,0:29:01.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,こう言ったんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.17,0:29:04.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,「都市と神殿は建て直される
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.17,0:29:07.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,そしてメシアが現れる」と
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.30,0:29:12.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,エフェル 新しい神殿を\N見ることができるよ
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.22,0:29:15.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,旅は危険じゃないですか？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.02,0:29:22.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはご自分の民を\N助けたいと思っている
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.86,0:29:25.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,イザヤにこう告げた
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.19,0:29:29.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,「生まれる子たちが苦しむことはない
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.57,0:29:35.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らとその子孫は エホバに\N祝福された民だからである」
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.29,0:29:36.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが言ったことは・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.87,0:29:38.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,必ず起きる！
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.96,0:29:41.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも土地は荒れています
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.83,0:29:46.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,だから腕のいい職人さんが\N大勢必要なんだよ
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.34,0:29:50.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルもユダに一緒に行くの？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.51,0:29:57.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,いやあ 行きたいなあ
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.52,0:30:06.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず道路の整備をお願いします
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.90,0:30:10.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,雨期になったら工事は難しいですから
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.86,0:30:12.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,トゥラ 手配しなさい
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.99,0:30:16.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,それにしても\Nいろんなことを知ってますね
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.83,0:30:19.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,とんでもありません 私はただ・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.12,0:30:24.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,この国には 王のお役に立つ\N専門家が大勢いますから
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.84,0:30:28.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.67,0:30:31.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,スサの知事についてだが
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.80,0:30:34.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,更迭した方がよいか？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.64,0:30:37.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,調べてもらいましたが
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.06,0:30:41.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,その知事は国のお金を着服していました\N間違いありません
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.98,0:30:43.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,そんなはずはない！
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.77,0:30:45.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの親族だったな オタネス
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.82,0:30:49.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,はい そうです そんなことをする\N人間ではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.74,0:30:51.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,何かの間違いでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.82,0:30:56.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼のことはダニエルよりも\N私の方がよく知っています
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.45,0:31:01.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,私がきちんと話をつけておきましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.62,0:31:04.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,メディア人とペルシャ人は寛容です
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.29,0:31:06.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダヤ人たちよりも
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.50,0:31:09.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,こちらで何とかします
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.67,0:31:14.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいだろう 迅速にな 頼んだぞ
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.76,0:31:55.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,お断りしたんですが 勝手に・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.69,0:32:12.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,よくもまあこんなに祈れるもんですね
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.28,0:32:16.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,王にお仕えするには神の助けが必要です
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.95,0:32:19.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,王に仕える？
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.24,0:32:22.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,知事を首にしてですか？
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.25,0:32:24.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,当然のことをしたまでです
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.29,0:32:28.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,よそ者にあれこれ指図されると\N迷惑なんですよね
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.92,0:32:31.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,王のためです
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.01,0:32:36.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネブカドネザル王にしたことも\N聞きましたよ
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.51,0:32:40.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたのせいで気が狂った
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.27,0:32:42.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,あれはエホバが語ったことです
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.39,0:32:43.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,知りませんよ
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.69,0:32:47.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,ただ 私たちの邪魔はしないでください
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.61,0:32:50.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,知事1人首にするのと
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.53,0:32:54.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダヤ人の年寄り1人片付けるのと
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.53,0:32:58.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,どっちが簡単かよく考えてください
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.77,0:33:26.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,お呼びでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.44,0:33:28.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜ呼ばれたか分かっているだろうな？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.90,0:33:30.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいえ
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.36,0:33:33.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルが問題にした知事だが
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.32,0:33:35.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後どうなったんだ？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.53,0:33:38.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,われわれもその件を\Nしっかり調査しました
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.83,0:33:40.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,問題はなかったのか？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.58,0:33:41.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,ありません
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.00,0:33:43.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,一つもか？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.37,0:33:45.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,はい
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.42,0:33:48.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,税は全て国に納められていたのか？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.63,0:33:53.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,金もビールも全てきちんと\N納められていました
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.22,0:33:57.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルの話とは随分違うな
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.72,0:33:59.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルですか
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.35,0:34:02.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,バビロンの時代には\N活躍していましたね・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.18,0:34:04.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,あの年では・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.23,0:34:08.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,つまり あの年できちんと\N仕事ができるのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.56,0:34:11.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,考えが古いんです
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.19,0:34:13.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかもユダヤ人ですよ
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.99,0:34:16.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,われわれは民族で差別はしない
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.36,0:34:18.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,ええ 私も差別には反対です
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.37,0:34:21.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル いいところに来た
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.29,0:34:24.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは正しかった
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.37,0:34:27.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,スサの住民が暴動を起こした
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.38,0:34:32.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,ピンはねをする\Nあの知事を替えてくれと
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.50,0:34:33.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,いや そんなはずは・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.59,0:34:35.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいかげんにしろ！
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.05,0:34:39.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,私が自分で調べたんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.97,0:34:46.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル あなたに並ぶ者は誰もいない
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.40,0:34:53.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,総理大臣になってくれたら\Nとても心強いのだが・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.40,0:34:59.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,王に直訴しますか
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.45,0:35:03.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,無駄だ 王はダニエルの言いなりだ
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.33,0:35:06.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルを訴えるしかない\N王が見過ごせない罪状で
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.87,0:35:08.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼は清廉潔白です
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.79,0:35:10.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,探せばある
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.34,0:35:13.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,人を集めて書類を調べさせろ
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.46,0:35:15.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,何か出てくるはずだ
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.84,0:35:19.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,そっちは 商人や役人を調べ上げろ
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.59,0:35:22.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰でもいい 協力者を探すんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.68,0:35:26.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,協力者には しっかり渡してやれ
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.31,0:35:29.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,バビロニア時代の記録もある\Nなんでもいい
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.73,0:35:32.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,使えるねたを探し出せ
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.01,0:36:00.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,何も出てきませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.72,0:36:02.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうだ？
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.10,0:36:05.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,どれも金額はぴったりです
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.02,0:36:08.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルが扱うようになってから
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.60,0:36:12.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,腐敗も無駄もなくなりました
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.36,0:36:15.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,何か見つけてくれ
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.70,0:36:22.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰も悪口を言わない
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.87,0:36:26.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんなに慕われている
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.79,0:36:32.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,王の信頼もあつい
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.92,0:36:38.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,普通 外国人の商人は
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.22,0:36:41.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,だまされても泣き寝入り\Nするしかないのに
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.84,0:36:45.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは外国人のために調査までする
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.22,0:36:50.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして きちんと弁償させる
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.15,0:36:54.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつも一緒にいた3人の評判もいい
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.94,0:36:59.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,その3人はバビロンの神を崇拝せず
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.20,0:37:01.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,火の中に放り込まれた
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.24,0:37:06.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 彼らの神エホバとやらに\N守られ 無傷だった
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.66,0:37:10.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかの神々を崇拝しないのか？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.75,0:37:13.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのようです
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.29,0:37:16.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは使えるな
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.21,0:37:22.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,カトゥ オタネス 今度は何の用だ？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.05,0:37:25.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダリウス王がいつまでも\N生き続けますように
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.22,0:37:29.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,バビロンは強固な都市ですが\N人種のるつぼです
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.18,0:37:33.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,バビロニア人 エジプト人 ギリシャ人\Nその他もろもろです
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.65,0:37:36.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,そんなことは知っている
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.19,0:37:41.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは王ですが 外国人であり\N征服したばかりです
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.32,0:37:43.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの権威を示さないと
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.57,0:37:46.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,国は不安定になってしまいます
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.58,0:37:49.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,何が言いたいんだ？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.45,0:37:52.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたに仕える役人や長官
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.58,0:37:56.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,知事や高官 総督が皆で協議した結果
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.59,0:38:01.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,次のような法令を制定していただくのが\Nよいということになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.30,0:38:07.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,30日の間 王以外の人や神に\N請願をしてはならず
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.18,0:38:12.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,背いた者はライオンの穴に\N投げ込まれる という禁令です
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.23,0:38:17.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,スサで起きたような暴動を\N起こさせないためにも・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.70,0:38:25.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,王よ この法令を制定し
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.45,0:38:28.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご署名くださいますように
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.49,0:38:32.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうすれば変更できなくなります
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.50,0:38:37.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,メディアとペルシャの法律は\N取り消すことができないからです
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.43,0:38:49.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,この帝国は
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.47,0:38:54.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,いまだかつてないほどの\N平和と繁栄に浴している
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.02,0:38:58.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,最近スサで起きた暴動をはじめ
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.44,0:39:02.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,少数の過激派による同様の行為は
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.19,0:39:05.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和を脅かすものである
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.11,0:39:09.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,その平和は 何にも代え難い
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.16,0:39:13.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,この帝国によって与えられている\N今の自由を守り
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.62,0:39:16.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,またこの国の主権を守るため
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.96,0:39:22.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,私メディア人ダリウスは\N次の法令を定める
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.63,0:39:24.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,30日の間
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.01,0:39:29.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,王以外の人や神に請願をしてはならず
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.93,0:39:35.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,背いた者はライオンの穴に投げ込まれる
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.34,0:40:00.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,まさか祈らないですよね？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.42,0:40:02.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,アザルエル
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.22,0:40:09.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,君たちも知っている
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.60,0:40:11.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,敵も知っている
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.64,0:40:14.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は窓辺で祈っている
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.27,0:40:18.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,1日3回 毎日だ
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.11,0:40:22.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,もし 窓辺で祈るのをやめたら
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.28,0:40:27.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんなはどう思うだろう？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.28,0:40:30.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,祈るのをやめたと
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.41,0:40:32.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,それだけじゃない
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.79,0:40:36.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを捨てたと思われる
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.12,0:40:38.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,命と引き換えに
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.67,0:40:41.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは私の友だ
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.38,0:40:43.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを信頼すれば
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.63,0:40:45.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,報いてくださる
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.05,0:40:48.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのようにかは分からない
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.80,0:40:53.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも必ず
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.68,0:40:58.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,祈ってほしい\N私が信仰を貫けるように
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.90,0:41:02.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんなが信仰を貫けるように
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.07,0:41:04.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんなことがあっても
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.05,0:41:27.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,これをおまえにあげよう
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.81,0:41:38.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご飯できたわよ
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.37,0:41:53.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバ救う・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.62,0:42:00.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,強い手で 恐れない」
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.05,0:42:08.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバ
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.72,0:42:11.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,聞いてください
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.14,0:42:18.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,私が声を上げて呼ぶ時
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.02,0:42:22.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,親切を示し
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.98,0:42:28.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,答えてください
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.20,0:42:31.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバ
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.24,0:42:35.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,私はあなたの好意を得ようと努めます
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.00,0:42:40.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは私を助ける方
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.46,0:42:44.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,見捨てないでください
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.55,0:42:48.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,放っておかないでください
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.76,0:42:53.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の救いの神」
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.41,0:44:03.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,王がいつまでも生き続けますように
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.67,0:44:09.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご署名になった禁令によれば
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.92,0:44:14.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,30日の間 人や神に\N請願をする者がいれば・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.47,0:44:16.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん あなた以外にです・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.85,0:44:18.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,ライオンの穴に入れられますね？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.02,0:44:23.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,その通りだ メディアとペルシャの\N法律は取り消すことができない
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.52,0:44:25.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,何が言いたい？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.77,0:44:30.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルなんですが・・・\Nユダから連れてこられた・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.36,0:44:32.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,王に敬意を払わず
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.40,0:44:35.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの禁令を無視しています
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.20,0:44:41.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,日に3度 神に祈っています
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.17,0:44:50.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルが？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.64,0:45:00.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,そんなはずはない
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.10,0:45:02.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当か？
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.43,0:45:05.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,あれは確信犯です
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.48,0:45:09.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,目撃者はいたのか？
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.65,0:45:12.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たち5人全員です
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.65,0:45:14.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼は老人だ
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.99,0:45:17.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,判断が鈍ったのでは？
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.45,0:45:22.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,政府高官なので 立場は\Nわきまえているはずです
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.71,0:45:28.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,少し考える
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.75,0:45:29.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,逮捕しましょうか？
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.96,0:45:32.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,考えると言っているだろう！
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.23,0:46:30.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは見せしめにする
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.94,0:46:33.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,高官の立場を解き
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.07,0:46:35.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,明日の朝バビロンから追放する
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.70,0:46:36.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,お言葉ですが・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.91,0:46:39.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,民は 従わないなら\Nどうなるか分かるだろう
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.53,0:46:41.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですが法律では
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.66,0:46:46.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,「ライオンの穴に投げ込む」\Nとなっていますが
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.25,0:46:49.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,そういうことか！恥ずかしくないのか
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.92,0:46:53.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,メディアとペルシャの法律によれば
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.17,0:46:58.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,王が制定した禁令や法令は\N一切変更できません
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.22,0:47:04.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,王の栄誉と安泰を願ったまでです
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.03,0:47:22.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,では そのようにしろ
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.52,0:49:52.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたが常に仕えている神が
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.90,0:49:56.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたを救ってくださると\Nよいのだが・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.46,0:50:13.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,石をどけろ！
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.97,0:50:24.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.81,0:50:28.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.77,0:50:34.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,王がいつまでも生き続けますように
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.90,0:50:39.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,生きてたぞ！引き上げろ！
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.49,0:50:42.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,天使が助けてくれました
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.65,0:50:45.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の神が遣わして
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.91,0:50:48.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,ライオンの口をふさいでくれたので
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.70,0:50:50.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,無事です
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.79,0:50:54.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は神の前で潔白です
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.71,0:51:03.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,王に対しても何も悪いことは\Nしておりません
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.30,0:51:10.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,アルメニアは私が頂こう
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.14,0:51:12.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルもあっけなかったな
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.02,0:51:16.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,アルメニアの馬は騎兵隊で使える
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.23,0:51:19.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分でも乗りたいし
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.49,0:51:24.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいだろう\Nアルメニアはやるよ
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.49,0:51:28.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,私はバクトリア地方がいい\N宝石がある
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.87,0:51:33.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,早くもダニエルの領土の山分けですか？
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.79,0:51:37.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここにいたぞ！
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.17,0:51:42.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,何事だ？
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.09,0:51:46.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダリウス王への反逆の罪で逮捕する！
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.64,0:51:48.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはダニエルの話だろ！
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.81,0:51:51.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは逮捕された
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.31,0:51:57.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,今朝 無傷で穴から引き上げられた
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.19,0:51:59.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,あり得ない
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.40,0:52:01.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,ライオンは満腹だったのか？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.44,0:52:03.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,病気だったんですか？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.45,0:52:08.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,ライオンが病気？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.99,0:52:11.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,満腹だった？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.00,0:52:21.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族もろとも穴に放り込め
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.13,0:52:23.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,満腹かどうか分かるだろう
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.13,0:52:25.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,王よ どうかご勘弁を！
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.55,0:52:26.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,やめてください！
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.93,0:52:28.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,おやめください！
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.18,0:52:29.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,やめろ！
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.18,0:52:30.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,は 放せ！
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.14,0:52:31.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,お許しください！
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.31,0:52:32.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,放せ！
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.72,0:52:34.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,お願いします！
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.39,0:52:36.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,王よ！
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.19,0:52:41.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の王国の領土全域において
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.32,0:52:45.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,民はダニエルの神の前で\N畏れかしこまるように
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.49,0:52:48.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,この方こそ生きている神であり
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.45,0:52:52.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,永遠に存在されるからである\Nこの方の王国は決して滅ぼされない
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.70,0:52:55.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,この方は人を助け 救い
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.41,0:52:59.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,天においても地においても奇跡や\N不思議なことを行われる
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.59,0:53:03.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルをライオンの\N爪から救ったのである
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.51,0:53:05.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダリウスが書かせたんですか？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.26,0:53:07.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,国中に書き送ったんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.51,0:53:09.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,心配したんですよ
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.68,0:53:11.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,怖かった？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.85,0:53:17.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,怖かったよ でもそういうときに\Nエホバは助けてくれる
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.27,0:53:20.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,パパとママ エルサレムに\N行くのが怖いんだって
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.69,0:53:23.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,エフェルったら！
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.11,0:53:27.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,まだ悩んでます
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.49,0:53:29.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは？帰るよね？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.78,0:53:33.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,王様 みんな帰っていいって言ってるよ
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.29,0:53:42.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,帰りたいよ
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.39,0:53:56.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.15,0:54:02.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちょっと遅過ぎたかな
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.58,0:54:14.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,僕も行きたくない
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.62,0:54:17.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,そんなこと言わないで
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.75,0:54:27.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムは 私がいた時よりも\N素晴らしい町になる
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.88,0:54:31.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,預言がその通りになる
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.43,0:54:38.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,町はエホバを崇拝する人で\Nいっぱいになる
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.73,0:54:42.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,新しい神殿は
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.98,0:54:46.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界で一番美しい建物になる
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.22,0:55:12.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,お隣のおじいちゃんに会った？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.47,0:55:14.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日は会ってないわ
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.76,0:55:18.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,おかしいのよエリったら\Nこの間もね・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.26,0:55:58.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバから離れてはいけないよ
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.35,0:56:01.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは共にいてくださる
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.03,0:56:19.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私は1つのことをエホバに願い求めた
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.50,0:56:28.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,今も強く願っている
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.47,0:56:35.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,一生涯エホバの家に住むことを
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.77,0:56:46.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.86,0:56:52.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,麗しさを見つめ
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.08,0:57:00.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の神殿を
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.08,0:57:04.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,感嘆して
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.42,0:57:09.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,眺めることを」
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.48,0:58:09.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル 少し休みましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.29,0:59:09.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,大切な人ダニエル
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.88,0:59:12.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は遣わされてきました
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.96,0:59:16.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,恐れることはありません
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.76,0:59:20.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたが謙遜になろうと\N心に決めた最初の日から
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.64,0:59:22.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,祈りは聞かれています
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.85,0:59:25.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,私が来たのは 最後の日々に
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.23,0:59:29.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの民に起きる事柄を\N理解させるためです
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.27,0:59:31.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう力が出ません
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.90,0:59:34.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,息をするのも大変です
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.78,0:59:38.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,大切な人ダニエル\N恐れることはありません
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.99,0:59:41.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,大丈夫です
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.12,0:59:44.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,勇気を出してください
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.30,0:59:56.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,お話しください
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.80,0:59:59.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,力が湧いてきました
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.59,1:00:03.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,真実の書に記されている事柄を伝えます
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.14,1:00:07.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,「さらに3人の王がペルシャの\Nために立ち上がります
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.27,1:00:12.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,4人目の王は他の王たちよりも\N多くの富を築きます」
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.33,1:00:34.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,これらの事柄はどんな結末を\N迎えるのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.13,1:00:38.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,待ち続ける人は幸せです！
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.26,1:00:42.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,最後まで進んでいきなさい
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.64,1:00:45.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは休みますが 日々の終わりに
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.64,1:00:49.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,報いを受けるために立ち上がります
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.71,1:01:10.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 食べると神に背くことになります
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.88,1:01:13.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,神を畏れているのか？
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.09,1:01:15.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうです
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.05,1:01:21.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の神エホバなら解き明かせます
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.43,1:01:24.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,必ず夢を解き明かしてくださいます
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.35,1:01:28.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.52,1:01:32.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご自分の民を助けたいと思っている
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.53,1:01:41.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは私の友だ
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.20,1:01:46.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを信頼すれば
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.79,1:01:52.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,報いてくださる
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.39,1:02:08.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのようにかは分からない
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.10,1:02:12.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも必ず
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.09,1:02:28.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当に励まされました
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.31,1:02:35.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルのように 私たちも\Nエホバから力と保護を得られます
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.85,1:02:39.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,次の歌でエホバへの信頼を表せます
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.52,1:02:43.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,歌の題は 「救いのために\N神に頼る」です
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.94,1:02:47.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,この150番の歌を歌いましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.87,1:02:51.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう一度言います 150番の歌です
